Henri Kontinen -LRB- born 19 June 1990 -RRB- is a Finnish tennis player .
Kontinen has won 14 doubles titles on the ATP Tour in his career .
On 18 October 2010 , Kontinen reached his best singles rankings of world number 220 .
He is currently ranked as world number 1 in doubles rankings after winning the Australian Open men 's doubles championship .
His brother Micke is a retired tennis player .
After ending his singles career due to injuries he started focusing on doubles .
He reached the quarterfinals of the men 's doubles 2016 Wimbledon Championships with John Peers and won the mixed doubles at the same tournament with Heather Watson .
He also won the 2017 Australian Open men 's doubles title with John Peers , reaching his first Grand Slam title in doubles .